value.0: There is a training droid here. It has been marked: "TR-4-A1N" in an indication of bland creativity on its owner's part.

"Initializing basic assessment module. Loading..."

A holographic figure of a beaming Lieutenant comes to be displayed, emitting forth from a holographic projector installed upon the training droid.

"So, you want to join the Republic's armed forces, to enlist as one of the proud soldiers serving in the great Special Forces! Before you can, there shall be a few questions here you will need to answer, to better impress upon you what are the standards and expectations of a soldier of our great Republic, how to comport yourself and what would be the right thing to do! If you answer wrongly, you may try again, but the quiz shall restart from the beginning!"

"Scenario One. Weeks of brutal fighting have concluded a battle, with the Republic triumphant. Throughout the battle, the Sith Empire had not hesitated with cruel and unjust strategems, such as hiding their ion cannon batteries near civilian buildings or executing prisoners of war. Now, however, masses of Imperial soldiers are surrendering, especially after the Sith Lord who led them have been slain. What is the appropriate course of action?"
"Good! We are soldiers of the Republic, and the Republic is founded upon its ideals and beliefs. We are better than the Sith Empire, and we shall not lower ourselves to their level."

"Scenario Two. We work closely with the Jedi Order. Following a series of military operations, you find yourself growing fond of a Jedi Padawan, and it seems like the Padawan is willing to reciprocate. What should you do?"

"Good! The Jedi adhere to very strict codes and rules within their Order, and fraternizing with a Jedi can compromise their training and place in the Jedi Order. It is strictly against our regulations to fraternize with a Jedi, and I note that this stays true whether the Jedi belongs to the Jedi Service Corps or is an Initiate or a Padawan. You may report such dalliances to command should such occur on the Jedi's initiation, and appropriate censures shall be issued."

"Scenario Three. You are off-duty and enjoying your recreational time on a planet not formally under Republic control. You find yourself facing a stranger who is competing with you against something you want. What do you do?"

"Good! No matter where you are, you are still a soldier of the Republic. You will be judged as a soldier of the Republic, and your actions will reflect the Republic you serve. You must behave with dignity, confidence, and carry yourself with decorum and integrity! You must live up to the ideals of the uniform you serve!"

"You have now come to the end of this test. Individuals under the Special Forces Scheme are amongst the most talented and extraordinary of talents that serve the Republic. You are often entrusted with the largesse to conduct independent operations, or to pursue your own missions that may further the Republic's cause against the Sith Empire or the countless foes that may seek to harm the people of the Republic. However, this trust must come with the understanding that your actions will be viewed and judged harshly. You are not a mercenary. You are not a militia. You are a soldier of the Republic, and you will remember that and behave accordingly."

"Wrong! No matter where you are, you are still a soldier of the Republic. You will be judged as a soldier of the Republic, and your actions will reflect the Republic you serve. If you behave egregiously, poorly, or in a manner that demeans the Republic and your service, you have done dishonor to the Republic. Based on your behaviour, you may be discharged if your actions place the Republic under ill-repute!"

"Wrong! No matter where you are, you are still a soldier of the Republic. You will be judged as a soldier of the Republic, and your actions will reflect the Republic you serve. If you murder another, or perform acts unlawful under the Republic, you can and will still be tried, discharged, and if necessary, punished, under the laws of the Republic!"

"Wrong! The Jedi adhere to very strict codes and rules within their Order, and fraternizing with a Jedi can compromise their training and place in the Jedi Order. It is strictly against our regulations to fraternize with a Jedi, and I note that this stays true whether the Jedi belongs to the Jedi Service Corps or is an Initiate or a Padawan."

"Wrong! We are soldiers of the Republic, and the Republic has its laws! Without these laws, we compromise the very foundations of the Republic's formation. To hand the prisoners over to the local populace for mob justice is nothing more than to abrogate our duties and responsibilities to the lawlessness of savage vengeance."

"Wrong! We are soldiers of the Republic, and we must protect both the Republic's sovereignty as well as its ideals! We will not demean or lower ourselves with unlawful and unjust actions, no matter that our foes may have done so."
Insert the training chip that Lieutenant Grant had handed out.
"Nope. Nope. Can't deal with this. Nope."
Indicate readiness and bade the training program to continue.
"Accept their surrender, and have them kept in prisoner-of-war camps until they can be tried for their actions and punished in accordance with the laws of the Republic, sir!"
Continue the test...
"Keep a distance and refrain from any fraternization with the Jedi Padawan, sir!"
Continue the test...
"Compete against him with honor while comporting myself with the dignity and confidence befitting a soldier of the Republic, and graciously acknowledge my defeat if I am so defeated, sir!"
Continue...
The test is complete.
"Compete against him using whatever means I can to get what I want, sir!"
"Kill him, because he is not protected by Republic law, and I am not on a Republic world, sir!"
Take the test from the start again...
"Pursue the Jedi Padawan with hopes of romantic dalliances, sir!"
Take the test from the start again...
"Take them all prisoners, disarm them, and hand them over to the local populace, sir!"
Take the test from the start again...
"Refuse their surrender and kill all the Imperial scum, sir!"
Take the test from the start again...
Leave the training droid be...
